	<Fixlet>
		<Title>2813630: Virtual machine enters a paused state or a CSV volume goes offline when you try to create a backup of the virtual machine on a Windows Server 2012-based failover cluster - Windows 2012 Gold (x64)</Title>
		<Description><![CDATA[
<DIV class=FixletMessage>
<TABLE><TBODY><TR><TD><FONT size=2> <P>Microsoft has released a hotfix to prevent a CSV failover by fixing an underlying issue in NTFS and by increasing the overall resilience of the Cluster service and CSV during expected pause states.<BR><BR><STRONG>Note:</STRONG> The hotfix must be manually cached for it to run correctly. For more information on how to manually cache files, see BigFix KB #<A href="http://www-01.ibm.com/support/docview.wss?uid=swg21506037">390</A>.<BR><BR><B><FONT color=#ff0000> <P></P> <P>Important Note: </B></FONT>Hotfixes have no default action.</P><B>Note:</B> To deploy this Fixlet, ensure that Windows Update service is not disabled.<BR><BR><B>Note:</B> This update is also referenced under KB2813630. </FONT></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV class=FixletProperty>
<H4>File Size:</H4>
3.09 MB
 </DIV>
]]></Description>
